articles.description:
Good illustration of why commodities like oil tend to be shitty investments over time https://twitter.com/corry_wang/status/1676947769456508928

Corry Wang: It’s always fascinating to be reminded that Moore’s law applies to power consumption as much as it does to dollar cost
From 2016 to 2020, Telefonica and Cogent’s datacenters tripled their served traffic, while energy consumption fell by -2% and -50% (!) respectively https://t.co/NSDVaCoROU
